article.headline: Old Dominion 72, Georgia St. 64
article.story: ATLANTA (AP) -- Brian Henderson scored 19 points and Old Dominion controlled most of the contest to beat Georgia State 72-64 on Saturday night. The Panthers (2-4, 0-1 Colonial Athletic Association) took a 30-28 lead in the first half when Justin Billingslea scored on a layup. Billingslea finished with 13 points and four rebounds. Old Dominion (4-4, 1-0) responded with a 15-2 run to finish the half. Henderson, who sparked the run with a 3-pointer, scored eight points during the spurt. Gerald Lee, who finished with 13 points, made a jumper with 15:25 left in the second half to give the Monarchs 53-38 lead -- their largest lead of the game. Georgia State rallied and cut the lead to 65-60 with 3:13 remaining in the game on a layup by Billingslea. But the Panthers didn't get any closer as Old Dominion guards Henderson and Brandon Johnson made their free throws down the stretch. Johnson finished with 12 points and four assists, while Jonathan Adams added 10 points for the Monarchs. Leonard Mendez led Georgia State with 16 points. Rashad Chase scored seven points and had 10 rebounds.
